/*!
\page kdgpu_api_overview KDGpu API Overview
\brief Comprehensive overview of the KDGpu graphics API and its mapping to Vulkan

\tableofcontents

\section kdgpu_api_intro Introduction

KDGpu is a modern, type-safe C++ wrapper around the Vulkan graphics API. It provides a simplified, high-level interface while maintaining complete control over the underlying Vulkan resources. KDGpu's design philosophy focuses on:

- <b>Type Safety</b>: Strong typing through handles and enums
- <b>Resource Management</b>: Handle-based ownership model with automatic resource cleanup
- <b>Simplicity</b>: Reduced boilerplate compared to raw Vulkan
- <b>Performance</b>: Zero-cost abstractions over Vulkan
- <b>Familiarity</b>: API structure closely mirrors Vulkan concepts

\section kdgpu_api_architecture API Architecture

The KDGpu API is organized into several logical groups:

\subsection kdgpu_api_arch_core Core Instance & Device Management
- \ref KDGpu::Instance "Instance" - Application-wide Vulkan instance ([VkInstance](https://registry.khronos.org/vulkan/specs/1.3-extensions/man/html/VkInstance.html))
- \ref KDGpu::Adapter "Adapter" - Physical GPU device ([VkPhysicalDevice](https://registry.khronos.org/vulkan/specs/1.3-extensions/man/html/VkPhysicalDevice.html))
- \ref KDGpu::Device "Device" - Logical device for GPU operations ([VkDevice](https://registry.khronos.org/vulkan/specs/1.3-extensions/man/html/VkDevice.html))
- \ref KDGpu::Queue "Queue" - Command submission queue ([VkQueue](https://registry.khronos.org/vulkan/specs/1.3-extensions/man/html/VkQueue.html))
- \ref KDGpu::Surface "Surface" - Window surface for presenting ([VkSurfaceKHR](https://registry.khronos.org/vulkan/specs/1.3-extensions/man/html/VkSurfaceKHR.html))

\subsection kdgpu_api_arch_resources GPU Resources
- \ref KDGpu::Buffer "Buffer" - GPU memory buffer ([VkBuffer](https://registry.khronos.org/vulkan/specs/1.3-extensions/man/html/VkBuffer.html))
- \ref KDGpu::Texture "Texture" - Image/texture resource ([VkImage](https://registry.khronos.org/vulkan/specs/1.3-extensions/man/html/VkImage.html))
- \ref KDGpu::TextureView "TextureView" - View into a texture ([VkImageView](https://registry.khronos.org/vulkan/specs/1.3-extensions/man/html/VkImageView.html))
- \ref KDGpu::Sampler "Sampler" - Texture sampling configuration ([VkSampler](https://registry.khronos.org/vulkan/specs/1.3-extensions/man/html/VkSampler.html))

\subsection kdgpu_api_arch_pipelines Pipelines & Shaders
- \ref KDGpu::GraphicsPipeline "GraphicsPipeline" - Graphics rendering pipeline ([VkPipeline](https://registry.khronos.org/vulkan/specs/1.3-extensions/man/html/VkPipeline.html))
- \ref KDGpu::ComputePipeline "ComputePipeline" - Compute shader pipeline ([VkPipeline](https://registry.khronos.org/vulkan/specs/1.3-extensions/man/html/VkPipeline.html))
- \ref KDGpu::RayTracingPipeline "RayTracingPipeline" - Ray tracing pipeline ([VkPipeline](https://registry.khronos.org/vulkan/specs/1.3-extensions/man/html/VkPipeline.html))
- \ref KDGpu::ShaderModule "ShaderModule" - SPIR-V shader module ([VkShaderModule](https://registry.khronos.org/vulkan/specs/1.3-extensions/man/html/VkShaderModule.html))
- \ref KDGpu::PipelineLayout "PipelineLayout" - Pipeline resource layout ([VkPipelineLayout](https://registry.khronos.org/vulkan/specs/1.3-extensions/man/html/VkPipelineLayout.html))
- \ref KDGpu::PipelineCache "PipelineCache" - Pipeline creation cache ([VkPipelineCache](https://registry.khronos.org/vulkan/specs/1.3-extensions/man/html/VkPipelineCache.html))
- \ref KDGpu::RenderPass "RenderPass" - Render pass configuration ([VkRenderPass](https://registry.khronos.org/vulkan/specs/1.3-extensions/man/html/VkRenderPass.html))

\subsection kdgpu_api_arch_descriptors Descriptors & Bindings
- \ref KDGpu::BindGroup "BindGroup" - Resource descriptor set ([VkDescriptorSet](https://registry.khronos.org/vulkan/specs/1.3-extensions/man/html/VkDescriptorSet.html))
- \ref KDGpu::BindGroupLayout "BindGroupLayout" - Descriptor set layout ([VkDescriptorSetLayout](https://registry.khronos.org/vulkan/specs/1.3-extensions/man/html/VkDescriptorSetLayout.html))
- \ref KDGpu::BindGroupPool "BindGroupPool" - Descriptor set pool ([VkDescriptorPool](https://registry.khronos.org/vulkan/specs/1.3-extensions/man/html/VkDescriptorPool.html))

\subsection kdgpu_api_arch_commands Command Recording
- \ref KDGpu::CommandBuffer "CommandBuffer" - Recorded GPU commands ([VkCommandBuffer](https://registry.khronos.org/vulkan/specs/1.3-extensions/man/html/VkCommandBuffer.html))
- \ref KDGpu::CommandRecorder "CommandRecorder" - Records GPU commands ([VkCommandBuffer](https://registry.khronos.org/vulkan/specs/1.3-extensions/man/html/VkCommandBuffer.html))
- \ref KDGpu::RenderPassCommandRecorder "RenderPassCommandRecorder" - Records rendering commands
- \ref KDGpu::ComputePassCommandRecorder "ComputePassCommandRecorder" - Records compute commands
- \ref KDGpu::RayTracingPassCommandRecorder "RayTracingPassCommandRecorder" - Records ray tracing commands

\subsection kdgpu_api_arch_sync Synchronization
- \ref KDGpu::Fence "Fence" - CPU-GPU synchronization ([VkFence](https://registry.khronos.org/vulkan/specs/1.3-extensions/man/html/VkFence.html))
- \ref KDGpu::GpuSemaphore "GpuSemaphore" - GPU-GPU synchronization ([VkSemaphore](https://registry.khronos.org/vulkan/specs/1.3-extensions/man/html/VkSemaphore.html))

\subsection kdgpu_api_arch_presentation Presentation
- \ref KDGpu::Swapchain "Swapchain" - Image presentation chain ([VkSwapchainKHR](https://registry.khronos.org/vulkan/specs/1.3-extensions/man/html/VkSwapchainKHR.html))

\subsection kdgpu_api_arch_raytracing Ray Tracing (Extensions)
- \ref KDGpu::AccelerationStructure "AccelerationStructure" - Ray tracing acceleration structure ([VkAccelerationStructureKHR](https://registry.khronos.org/vulkan/specs/1.3-extensions/man/html/VkAccelerationStructureKHR.html))
- \ref KDGpu::RayTracingShaderBindingTable "RayTracingShaderBindingTable" - Ray tracing shader binding table

\subsection kdgpu_api_arch_queries Query Operations
- \ref KDGpu::TimestampQueryRecorder "TimestampQueryRecorder" - GPU timestamp queries ([VkQueryPool](https://registry.khronos.org/vulkan/specs/1.3-extensions/man/html/VkQueryPool.html))

\section kdgpu_api_ownership Resource Ownership Model

KDGpu uses a handle-based resource management system. See \ref kdgpu_handle_ownership for details.

<b>Key principles:</b>
- Frontend KDGpu resources (e.g. Texture, Buffer) are wrappers around Vulkan resources
- Frontend KDGpu resources use handles to safely reference underlying Vulkan wrapped resources
- Resources lifetime is RAII-based, automatically cleaned up when owning objects are destroyed
- Move semantics: Resources can be moved but not copied
- Reference invalidation: Handles become invalid when resources are destroyed

